Your implementation differs from ours in that you're creating a single class for checking a fixed set of points, whereas our method supports polygons of any size and shape by defining multiple PolygonRegion objects for different zones. If you wish to continue with your current approach, you'll need to create either a Pose2d or Translation2d array for each point in your polygon. For instance:

```java
Translation2d[] yellowRegion = new Translation2d[]{
    new Translation2d(4.501, 6.176),
    new Translation2d(8.768, 8.000)
};
```

This example demonstrates how to represent a two-point polygon that can be published using a StructArrayPublisher, displaying it as a line in AdvantageScope. Here’s an illustration of a Translation2d array representing a triangular loading station zone:

```java
